son32java.son32reader

Interface Son32JavaInterface

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.sun.jna.Library

    public interface Son32JavaInterface
extends com.sun.jna.Library
    This interface represents the "map" between the son32.cll (c code) and the Son32Reader (java code). All used methodes are declared here according to their signature in the son32.h header file. The interface can not be implemented, because this would force to override the methodes.

                                      com.sun.jna.Memory pFltMask)
        This function reads contiguous waveform data from the given channel between two set times.
        Parameters:
        fh - The file descriptor for the .smr file
        chan - The number of the channel (counting starts with 0).
        pFloat - Points to the area of memory in which any data found is to be returned.
        max - The max number of data point that may be returned.
        sTime - The strat time in clock ticks.
        eTime - The end time in clock ticks.
        pbTime - The time of the first returned data point in clock ticks.
        pFltMask - Filter for AdcMark channels, ignored if null.
        Returns:
        The number of returned data points.
